<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-13T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-13T14:00:00-05:00" n="985" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d985">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.48/3080</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Arredondo</persName>, representing American
                                interests in Mexico</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-13T14:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 13, 1916, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>330. See Department’s 286, March 20, and hand copy thereof to Rodgers,
                            for his information. Telegraph number Americans, especially women and
                            children, that have followed advice in said instruction, and again
                            advise Americans, whose presence in Mexico City is not absolutely
                            essential for business reasons, to return to this country.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>